          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            You know you're in form when you win 6-0 without playing particularly well! Alexis' chip was delightful, Walcott's goal was an excellent strike and Oezil showed why for so many Arsenal fans it is a shock to not see him score a double figure number of goals every season. A lot of it was timidness, he would often pass rather than shoot for whatever reason but Wenger has obviously been drilling it in how much of a goal threat he can be and we saw with his finishes tonight what a class all-round number 10 he can be. I didn't like how open we were but I'm sure that was largely because Ludogorets lack an end product. There were lots of nice passes in the first 2 thirds but minimal execution in the danger zone. It was good to see the Ox score. Chances are Iwobi will start against Middlesbrough but I wonder if it might be a good idea to rest Oezil in that game, play Iwobi in the 10 and Alex LW. Build his confidence a bit. Coquelin had a good game considering he was injured too.
